sources.title: King Dinosaur (1955) BURT I. GORDON
sources.description:
It's Friday@PizzaFLIX
Writer/Director: Bert I. Gordon
Stars: William Bryant, Wanda Curtis, Douglas Henderson

Atomic Age and Stone Age collide when a new planet appears in our solar system. From afar, it appears similar in characteristics to Earth, but four space explorers discover it's home to giant monsters that are fatal to their survival.

metadata.Plot: Blasting off to a newly discovered planet called Nova, which moved into our solar system, four explorers behold a fantastic adventure. The mysterious new planet has similar characteristics of Earth, except it is home to terrifying monsters like giant snakes, giant ants, mutated alligators, and most terrifying of all, King Dinosaur, a strange lizard-like being that is a fatal threat to the explorers. Can these people survive this planet and escape?
metadata.Writer: Bert I. Gordon, Al Zimbalist, Tom Gries
metadata.Actors: William Bryant, Wanda Curtis, Douglas Henderson
